  "local_port": 39214,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "My H1b visa is under Admin processing for about a year now, and there's has been no update so far. What options do I have?",
  "response": "Experiencing a prolonged administrative processing period for your H-1B visa can be frustrating. Here are some steps you can consider taking:\n\n1. **Contact the Consulate/Embassy**: Reach out to the consulate or embassy where your interview was conducted. Sometimes, contacting them might provide additional insights or updates regarding your case.\n\n2. **Seek Assistance from the Petitioner's Company**: Inform your employer about the situation. Sometimes, having the employer reach out to U.S. Citizenship and Immigration Services (USCIS) or the consulate can expedite the process.\n\n3. **Inquire with a Senator or Congressman**: You can contact your local U.S. senator or congressional representative's office for assistance. They can sometimes intervene on your behalf to inquire about the status of your visa application.\n\n4. **File a Freedom of Information Act (FOIA) Request**: If you want more information about what may be causing the delay, filing a FOIA request can provide details about any decision-making or documentation issues.\n\n5. **Consider Legal Assistance**: Consulting with an immigration attorney can provide you with personalized advice tailored to your situation. An attorney can help navigate complex cases and provide additional options or insights.\n\n6. **Check Travel History and Documentation**: Ensure that there's no missing or problematic documentation, such as prior travel history or issues with submitted documents that might be causing the delay.\n\n7. **Wait and Monitor**: Continue to monitor your application status online using the U.S. Department of State's Consular Electronic Application Center (CEAC) website. While it\u2019s not ideal, in some cases, waiting is the only option.\n\nRemember, it's important to avoid making any assumptions about your case without verified information. Consult directly with reliable sources or legal professionals for guidance tailored to your specific circumstances.",
